      • serialize

        public abstract YAPIONObject serialize​(T object,
                                       YAPIONSerializer yapionSerializer)
        This method is used to serialize the type defined by type(). You will get the object to serialize as well as the current YAPIONSerializer designated to this serialization. This serializer should be used to serialize any parts of the Object that are not primitive types. So anything that cannot be represented by YAPIONValue. To use the serializer call YAPIONSerializer.parse(Object). You will need to provide the Object and the YAPIONSerializer will provide you with an YAPIONAny. This is generic and can be an YAPIONObject, YAPIONMap, YAPIONArray, YAPIONPointer or YAPIONValue. So you should be able to handle any thing you can get or just handle it generically with YAPIONAny to be safe.
        Specified by:
        serialize in interface SerializerObjectInterface<T>
        Parameters:
        object - the Object to serialize
        yapionSerializer - the current YAPIONSerializer
        Returns:
        the serialized version of the inputted Object

      • deserialize

        public abstract T deserialize​(YAPIONObject yapionObject,
                              YAPIONDeserializer yapionDeserializer)
        This method is used to deserialize the type defined by type(). You will get the specified YAPIONObject as well as the current YAPIONDeserializer designed to this deserialization. This deserializer should be used to deserialize any parts of the YAPIONObject that are not YAPIONValue types. So anything that cannot be represented by YAPIONValue. To use the serializer call YAPIONDeserializer.parse(YAPIONAny). You will need to provide the YAPIONAny and the YAPIONDeserializer will provide you with an Object. This is generic and can be any Object. So you should be able to handle any thing generically.
        Specified by:
        deserialize in interface SerializerObjectInterface<T>
        Parameters:
        yapionObject - The YAPIONObject to deserialize
        yapionDeserializer - the current YAPIONDeserializer
        Returns:
        the deserialized version of the inputted YAPIONObject
